- License: No explicit license (GitHub public repository, All Rights Reserved by default)
- Usage in this project: Referenced as an external Prompt library for academic writing.
  This project does not redistribute the content of awesome-ai-research-writing.
  Users should clone the upstream repository separately and comply with its terms.

### figures4papers

- Repository: https://github.com/ChenLiu-1996/figures4papers
- Author: Chen Liu (Yale University)
- License: No explicit license (GitHub public repository, All Rights Reserved by default)
- Usage in this project: The `skills/scientific-figure-making/` directory contains
  original usage guides and design references inspired by figures4papers.
  It does not include the original Python scripts or figure outputs from figures4papers.
  Users should visit the upstream repository for full scripts and demos.
